<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-01-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="64" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Governor of Pennsylvania</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-01-19"><hi rend="italic">January 19,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Please advise me when the trial of Sheriff Martin and his deputies will
                            take place. With the President’s approval it is desired to have a
                            representative of the Department of Justice attend the trial, but not to
                            take part therein, in view of the international questions which may
                            result.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sherman.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>